cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.CYBER, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of identifying pathogenic social media accounts, which involves analyzing user behavior and community detection. This falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), cybersecurity (cs.CR, cs.CYBER), and natural language processing (cs.CL) as the paper mentions the use of classification algorithms. Additionally, the use of causal inference to identify PSMs is a statistical approach that could be classified under the sub-category of social influence (cs.SI).
